                  <birth when="1827"/>
               <floruit notBefore="1847" notAfter="1855">He was <persName ref="PRS5205haylaMa">
                     <roleName type="title">nǝguś 
               </roleName>
                  </persName>
                   
                  of <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">
                  Šawā </placeName> from about <date>1827</date> to <date>1855</date>. 
                  He aspired to a central role in Ethiopian politics and he even took the title 
                  <persName ref="PRS5205haylaMa">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>Ḫāyla Malakot</persName> although he was not anointed. 
                  When  
                  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Tewodros II</persName> 
                  invaded <placeName ref="LOC6185Wallo">Wallo</placeName>, 
                  <persName ref="PRS5205haylaMa">Ḫāyla Malakot</persName> cooperated with the 
                  <placeName ref="LOC6185Wallo">Wallo</placeName> ruler, 
                  <persName ref="PRS10062Warqitu">Warqitu</persName> but their plan <!--which plan? DR 2018-05-24--> failed.
                  Then,  
                  <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName>
                     Tewodros II</persName> invaded <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">
                     Šawā </placeName> and <persName ref="PRS5205haylaMa">Ḫāyla Malakot</persName> was defeated and seriously wounded. </floruit>
                  
               <death when="1855">He died in <date>1855</date> 
                  and was buried <placeName ref="LOC2238DabraB">Dabra Baggǝʿ</placeName>.
               </death>
